snippet: A severe thunderstorm uprooted trees and left them scattered around the course at Congressional Country Club outside Washington, delaying the start of the third round.
abstract: Golf Roundup; delayed third round of the AT&T National is closed to spectators and volunteers for safety reasons after a powerful storm uproots large trees across the golf course; other golf news noted.
lead_paragraph: A severe thunderstorm uprooted trees and left them scattered around the course at Congressional Country Club outside Washington, delaying the start of the third round.

headline.seo: PGA Tour: Fans Barred, but Play Goes On After Storm Damage at AT&T National
headline.main: After a Storm Pummels Congressional, Clapping Could Be Mistaken for a Roar
